16/04/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- State railway company Zeleznice Srbije announced on Thursday (April 15th) that a group of masked hooligans attacked one of its trains late Wednesday, injuring seven people. In a statement, the company said that five attackers carrying guns, clubs and chains broke into a train at a station near Belgrade. Five passengers and two employees were injured before the attackers escaped. (AP, Beta, B92 - 15/04/10)
